    "product_description_tabs_PiVm7e": {
      "type": "product-description-tabs",
      "name": "Product Desc Tabs",
      "settings": {
        "description_content": "Elevate your piercing collection with premium 9K gold crafted into a hinged segment clicker ring—engineered for effortless insertion, everyday comfort, and timeless elegance across nose, ear, and cartilage piercings.",
        "specifications_content": "<h3>Technical Specifications</h3>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Specification</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Details</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Material</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">9K Solid Gold (37.5% pure gold with copper, silver, zinc alloy)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Available Finishes</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yellow Gold, White Gold, Rose Gold</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mechanism</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hinged Segment (opens and closes smoothly)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gauge Options</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G (1.2mm), 18G (1.0mm), 20G (0.8mm)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Inner Diameter Options</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">6mm, 7mm, 8mm, 9mm, 10mm, 11mm, 12mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hypoallergenic</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes—Implant-Grade Quality Certified</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nickel Content</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nickel-free or trace amounts below allergenic thresholds</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Body Parts</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nose (septum, nostril), ear (helix, daith, conch, tragus, cartilage)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Weight</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Not specified in the provided data</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Surface Finish</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">High-polish, mirror-bright</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
        "features_content": "<h3>Key Features &amp; Benefits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Hinged Segment Mechanism:</strong> Opens and closes smoothly for intuitive insertion and removal. No compression required. Ideal for newly-pierced piercings, sensitive placements, and everyday convenience.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>9K Solid Gold Construction:</strong> Premium material combines structural durability with hypoallergenic biocompatibility. Engineered to withstand mechanical stress from daily use while remaining skin-safe.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Implant-Grade Quality:</strong> Meets rigorous biocompatibility standards originally developed for surgical implants. Safe for new piercings, sensitive skin, and individuals with metal sensitivities.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Three Finish Options:</strong> Yellow gold, white gold, or rose gold—all solid 9K throughout. Never plating or coating; consistent quality across all colour variants.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Versatile Sizing:</strong> Three gauge options (16G, 18G, 20G) and seven inner diameter choices (6mm–12mm) accommodate diverse piercing types and personal aesthetic preferences.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Lightweight &amp; Comfortable:</strong> 9K gold provides substantial quality without weight pressure. No snagging on clothing or hair. Suitable for all-day wear, active lifestyles, and sleep.</li>\n</ul>",
        "how_to_use_content": "<h3>Insertion &amp; Removal Instructions</h3>\n<p>The hinged segment mechanism is intuitive, but following proper technique ensures smooth, comfortable use and protects your piercing.</p>\n<h4>Before Insertion</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>Wash your hands thoroughly with antibacterial soap and dry completely.</li>\n<li>Clean the hinged clicker ring under warm running water with mild soap. Dry with a soft cloth.</li>\n<li>Confirm your piercing is fully healed. For newly-pierced piercings, wait until your piercer confirms healing readiness.</li>\n<li>If unsure of your piercing's gauge, contact your original piercer—they have this specification on file.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Inserting the Ring</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<strong>Open the hinge gently:</strong> Hold the ring firmly and rotate the segment outward. The hinge should move smoothly—never force it.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Position the opening:</strong> Align the open segment directly toward your piercing channel.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Insert slowly:</strong> Guide the ring through your piercing with steady, gentle pressure. Rushed insertion increases discomfort.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Close the segment:</strong> Once fully inserted, gently rotate the segment back into place. You'll feel or hear a subtle click as it secures.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Verify security:</strong> Gently tug the ring to confirm it sits securely without rotating or sliding unexpectedly.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Removing the Ring</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>Wash your hands with antibacterial soap before touching your piercing.</li>\n<li>Gently open the hinge by rotating the segment outward with steady, even pressure.</li>\n<li>Slowly guide the ring out of your piercing. Do not rush or force.</li>\n<li>Clean the ring immediately and allow it to air dry completely.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Troubleshooting</h4>\n<p><strong>Difficult insertion?</strong> Do not force. For new piercings, swelling may cause temporary tightness. Rest for 12–24 hours and try again, or consult your piercer. <strong>Stiff hinge?</strong> Gentle cleaning with warm soapy water usually restores smooth movement. <strong>Persistent discomfort?</strong> Your gauge or diameter may not match your piercing. Consider consulting a professional piercer about sizing options.</p>",
        "care_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"care-instructions\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <h3>Cleaning, Maintenance &amp; Storage</h3>\n<h4>Daily Care</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Rinse under warm running water with mild, fragrance-free soap after removal.</li>\n<li>Gently clean all surfaces with your fingers or a soft cloth, including the hinge mechanism.</li>\n<li>Pat dry immediately with a soft, lint-free cloth.</li>\n<li>Avoid harsh or antibacterial soaps—residue dulls the finish.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Weekly Deep Clean</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Soak the ring in warm water with 1–2 drops of mild dish soap for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Use a soft-bristled toothbrush (dedicated to jewellery) to gently brush the entire ring and hinge.</li>\n<li>Rinse thoroughly under running water until all soap is removed.</li>\n<li>Dry completely with a soft cloth before storing.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Preventing Damage &amp; Tarnish</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Storage:</strong> Keep in a designated pouch or jewellery box, separate from other jewellery to prevent scratching.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Chemical exposure:</strong> Remove before swimming in chlorinated pools, using harsh cleaning products, or applying heavy cosmetics.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Temperature extremes:</strong> Avoid repeated exposure to very hot or cold environments, which stress the metal and hinge mechanism.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Moisture control:</strong> Store in a dry environment. Excessive moisture promotes oxidation and affects hinge smoothness.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Restoring Shine &amp; Professional Care</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>A soft microfibre cloth restores shine when the finish becomes matte. Rub gently in circular motions.</li>\n<li>This natural patina actually protects the underlying metal.</li>\n<li>Avoid commercial gold polishes with harsh chemicals.</li>\n<li>For significant buildup, a professional jeweller can clean and inspect the hinge mechanism.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Long-Term Storage</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Clean and dry thoroughly before extended storage.</li>\n<li>Wrap in a soft cloth or place in an airtight pouch to minimize air exposure.</li>\n<li>Store in a cool, dry location away from direct sunlight.</li>\n<li>Gently rotate the hinge mechanism monthly to keep it responsive during storage.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "materials_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"materials-quality\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <h3>9K Gold: Material Composition &amp; Why It's Optimal for Body Jewellery</h3>\n<p>9K gold (37.5% pure gold) is the ideal material for hinged clicker mechanisms. Higher purities—14K, 18K, 24K—are softer and cannot withstand the mechanical stress that a hinged ring experiences during daily insertion and removal.</p>\n<h4>Material Composition</h4>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Component</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Percentage</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Function in 9K Gold</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pure Gold</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">37.5%</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Provides hypoallergenic foundation and luxurious appearance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Copper</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">~40–50%</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Strengthens metal structure; enables hinge durability; creates yellow gold warmth</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Silver</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">~10–20%</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Enhances malleability during manufacturing; enables white and rose gold finishes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Zinc</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Trace amounts</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Increases hardness and corrosion resistance; nickel-free alternative for allergy protection</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h4>Why 9K Gold for Hinged Clickers?</h4>\n<p><strong>Structural Durability:</strong> The hinge opens and closes hundreds of times. Pure gold is too soft for this mechanical demand. 9K gold's alloy composition creates necessary hardness for reliable hinge function across extended use.</p>\n<p><strong>Hypoallergenic Biocompatibility:</strong> The alloy metals—copper, silver, zinc—are selected for skin safety. These don't trigger allergic reactions. The composition meets implant-grade standards, making 9K gold suitable for newly-pierced and sensitive piercings.</p>\n<p><strong>Cost-Effectiveness Without Compromise:</strong> Higher purities offer no functional benefit for body jewellery under mechanical stress. Extra gold content increases cost without improving hinge performance or skin compatibility.</p>\n<h4>Gold Purity Comparison</h4>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gold Type</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Purity</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Structural Durability</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hypoallergenic</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ideal For</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">9K Gold</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">37.5%</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Excellent</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes (implant-grade)</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hinged clickers, daily wear, and mechanical stress</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">14K Gold</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">58.3%</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Good</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Depends on the alloy</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Fine jewellery, lower mechanical demand</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">18K Gold</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">75%</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Fair</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Depends on the alloy</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Luxury pieces, minimal stress environments</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h4>Finish Variations: Solid Gold, Not Plating</h4>\n<p>All three finishes—yellow gold, white gold, rose gold—are solid 9K gold throughout. Never plating or coating over base metal. The visual difference comes from alloy composition: yellow gold has higher copper content (traditional warmth); white gold incorporates silver and whitening agents (contemporary refinement); rose gold has an elevated copper ratio (romantic aesthetic). Each finish maintains identical hypoallergenic, implant-grade quality.</p>\n<h4>Implant-Grade Certification</h4>\n<p>This clicker ring meets implant-grade biocompatibility standards—rigorous testing developed for surgical implants. Certification confirms: alloy composition tested for cytotoxicity (cell damage), sensitisation potential, and irritation risk. Nickel is absent or present only in trace amounts below allergenic thresholds. Material demonstrates hypoallergenic properties in clinical testing. While your ring is not a surgical implant, this standard ensures material safety for prolonged skin and piercing channel contact.</p>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "ideal_usages_content": "<div class=\"tab-content\" id=\"ideal-usages-styling\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <h3>Where &amp; How to Wear Your Gold Hinged Clicker Ring</h3>\n<h4>Single-Piercing Statement</h4>\n<p>A solitary 9K gold hinged clicker in your nostril or septum commands attention through material quality alone. The classic segment design reads as refined, not ostentatious. Perfect for minimalist aesthetics, professional environments, and occasions where one statement piece matters more than layered complexity.</p>\n<h4>Layered Ear Styling</h4>\n<p>Position this <strong>hinged ring</strong> across multiple ear piercings—helix, daith, conch, tragus. Consistent gold finish and similar silhouette create visual harmony; varied placements suggest intentional curation. Pair with complementary pieces in matching finishes for maximum cohesion. Space rings evenly for sophisticated balance or cluster in upper cartilage for bolder impact.</p>\n<h4>Nose &amp; Ear Coordination</h4>\n<p>Wear a <strong>gold nose ring clicker</strong> in your septum or nostril while sporting matching gold pieces in ear piercings. Coordinated metals tie your piercing aesthetic together, creating intentional, curated appearance across your collection.</p>\n<h4>Pairing with Body Jewellery</h4>\n<p>9K gold extends beyond ear and nose. Pair your <strong>solid gold clicker</strong> with gold belly rings or other body jewellery for coordinated full-body styling. Gold's timeless quality ensures pieces from different collections work together harmoniously.</p>\n<h4>Everyday Active Wear</h4>\n<p>The lightweight feel and smooth hinged mechanism make this ring comfortable for all-day wear—work, exercise, sleep, active lifestyles. No snagging on clothing or hair. No pressure points. It adapts to your life rather than demanding special handling.</p>\n<h4>Seasonal &amp; Occasion Styling</h4>\n<p><strong>Everyday:</strong> Yellow gold brings warmth to any outfit; traditional appeal grounds eclectic personal styles. <strong>Professional/Formal:</strong> White gold reads contemporary and refined; neutral tone complements business formal attire. <strong>Date Night/Evening:</strong> Rose gold's romantic warmth suits evening wear and catches light beautifully. <strong>Alternative Fashion:</strong> The hinged mechanism reads intentionally alternative without excess—perfect for punk, goth, avant-garde aesthetics.</p>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "size_guide_content": "<div class=\"tab-content\" id=\"gauge-size-guide\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <h3>Understanding Gauge &amp; Inner Diameter Selection</h3>\n<p>Selecting the correct gauge and inner diameter is essential for comfort, security, and aesthetic satisfaction. Your existing piercing was created at a specific gauge—most commonly 16G, 18G, or 20G. Your new clicker ring must match this gauge.</p>\n<h4>Gauge Explained</h4>\n<p>Gauge measures metal shaft thickness. Lower numbers = thicker metal. Your piercing requires a specific gauge or the ring will be too tight (smaller gauge) or too loose (larger gauge).</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gauge</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Measurement</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Typical Piercings</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Characteristics</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">1.2mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Standard ear, nose, septum, conch</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Most common for adult piercings. Sturdiest option.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">18G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">1.0mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Delicate ear, daith, helix, nostril</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Refined appearance for finer placements.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">20G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">0.8mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Fine nose piercings, upper helix</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thinnest option; suitable for petite placements.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h4>Inner Diameter Explained</h4>\n<p>Inner diameter measures the open space inside the ring in millimetres. It determines visual size and ring fit in your piercing.</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Inner Diameter</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Visual Style</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Best For</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Piercing Fit</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">6mm–7mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Snug, streamlined, delicate</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nostril, daith, helix, fine ear placements</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Compact appearance; minimal metal extension</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">8mm–9mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Balanced, versatile, statement-capable</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Septum, conch, standard cartilage</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Sweet spot for versatility; works across placements</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">10mm–12mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bold, dramatic, expansive</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Larger cartilage, septum stretch, statement wear</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Maximum visual impact; requires ample clearance</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h4>Sizing Recommendations by Piercing Type</h4>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Piercing Location</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Recommended Gauge</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Recommended Diameter</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Why This Combination</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nostril (Standard)</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">18G–20G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">7mm–8mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Most common nose piercing; comfortable everyday wear</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Septum</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G–18G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">8mm–10mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Larger diameter accommodates septum thickness; prevents tissue catching</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Helix</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G–18G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">6mm–8mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ear cartilage placements benefit from refined sizing</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Conch</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G–18G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">9mm–11mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thicker tissue; larger diameter prevents discomfort</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Daith</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G–18G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">6mm–7mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Intricate placement; smaller diameter maintains elegant proportions</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tragus</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G–18G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">7mm–8mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Flexible tissue; medium diameter accommodates movement</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">General Cartilage</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G–18G</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">7mm–9mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Versatile across ear positions and individual anatomy</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h4>How to Determine Your Gauge</h4>\n<p><strong>Contact your original piercer:</strong> Most reliable method. They created your piercing and have accurate gauge records. <strong>Visual comparison:</strong> If you have existing jewellery in the same gauge, compare metal thickness. <strong>Professional measurement:</strong> A piercing studio can measure your piercing using callipers.</p>\n<h4>Choosing Your Size with Confidence</h4>\n<p>If you're between sizes, err slightly smaller—a snug fit is safer than a loose fit, risking rotation or falling out. If insertion feels tight or uncomfortable, or if the ring rotates unexpectedly, you may need a different size. Monster Piercing offers hassle-free exchanges to find your perfect fit.</p>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "faq_content": "<div class=\"tab-content\" id=\"faq\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <ul class=\"faq-list\">\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What gauge options does this clicker ring come in?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>This 9K gold hinged clicker ring is available in three gauge options: 16G (1.2mm), 18G (1.0mm), and 20G (0.8mm). Gauge measures the thickness of the metal shaft. Your existing piercing was created at a specific gauge—most commonly 16G, 18G, or 20G. You must select a ring that matches your piercing's gauge, or it will be too tight or too loose. If you're unsure, contact your original piercer—they have your gauge specification on file.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            How do I choose the right inner diameter?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Inner diameter ranges from 6mm to 12mm and determines the visual size and ring fit. A 6mm–7mm diameter is snug and streamlined, ideal for nostril or daith piercings. An 8mm–9mm diameter offers versatility across septum, conch, and cartilage placements—this is the most popular choice. A 10mm–12mm diameter creates a bold, dramatic look for larger piercings or statement wear. If you're between sizes, choose slightly smaller for a secure fit.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Is this ring suitable for newly-pierced piercings?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>The 9K gold and implant-grade composition make this ring suitable for newly-pierced piercings in terms of material safety. However, timing is critical. Do not insert any jewellery into a fresh piercing until your piercer confirms full healing—typically 6–12 weeks depending on location. During healing, the piercing channel is delicate and vulnerable to infection. Once healed, the smooth hinged mechanism and implant-grade material make this an excellent choice for sensitive piercings.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What's the advantage of a hinged clicker mechanism?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>A hinged clicker opens and closes smoothly, allowing the segment to rotate outward. This makes insertion and removal intuitive—you don't force metal through your piercing. A fixed segment ring requires compressing and threading it through, which can be uncomfortable or painful. The hinged design also allows natural movement with your body, reducing irritation. For daily wearability and comfort, especially in newly-pierced placements, the hinged mechanism is functionally superior.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Can I wear this ring in multiple piercing locations?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Yes, this 9K gold hinged clicker works across nostril, septum, helix, conch, daith, tragus, and general cartilage piercings. You simply select the correct gauge and diameter combination for each location. For example, a nostril might be 18G with 8mm diameter, while a septum might be 16G with 10mm diameter. If you want to wear this ring across multiple piercings, you may need to purchase different size combinations for each location.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            How do I clean and maintain this 9K gold ring?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Daily cleaning is simple: rinse with warm water and mild soap, then dry with a soft cloth. Once weekly, soak in warm soapy water for 5 minutes and gently brush with a soft-bristled toothbrush, paying attention to the hinge mechanism. Avoid harsh chemicals, chlorinated pools, and extreme temperatures. Store in a dry, separate container. 9K gold naturally resists tarnishing, but environmental exposure and skin oils can dull the finish over time. A soft microfibre cloth restores shine. For significant buildup, a professional jeweller can clean and inspect the hinge mechanism.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What does 'implant-grade' mean?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Implant-grade indicates that the 9K gold meets biocompatibility testing standards originally developed for surgical implants. This certification means the material has been tested for cytotoxicity (cell damage), sensitization (allergic potential), and irritation. Implant-grade 9K gold contains nickel either not at all or only in trace amounts below allergenic thresholds. While your clicker is not a surgical implant, this certification ensures the material is safe for prolonged skin and piercing channel contact—particularly important for newly-pierced or sensitive piercings.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Is this ring hypoallergenic?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Yes, the 9K gold composition is hypoallergenic. The alloy metals mixed with gold—copper, silver, and zinc—are chosen specifically for biocompatibility and do not trigger allergic responses in sensitive individuals. However, if you have a known allergy to copper or specific metals, contact Monster Piercing before purchasing to verify exact alloy composition. Even implant-grade jewellery can cause reactions in individuals with severe metal sensitivities. If you experience irritation, itching, or discharge after insertion, remove the ring immediately and consult a healthcare provider.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Can I sleep in this clicker ring?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Sleeping in a hinged clicker ring is generally safe, but comfort depends on your piercing placement and sleeping position. For ear piercings (helix, daith, conch), the ring may press uncomfortably if you sleep on that side. For nose piercings, sleeping should be fine. During sleep, gentle movement can stress the hinge slightly—not dangerously, but allowing the mechanism rest extends its lifespan. If sleep comfort is a concern, remove the ring at night and reinsert in the morning; the hinged design makes this quick and easy.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What if the hinge feels stiff?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>A stiff hinge typically indicates buildup of skin oils, soap residue, or environmental dust in the mechanism. Clean as follows: soak in warm soapy water for 5 minutes, gently brush the hinge with a soft-bristled toothbrush, rinse thoroughly, and dry completely. This usually restores smooth movement. If stiffness persists, a tiny amount of sterile saline or a jeweller's lubricant (applied sparingly and wiped immediately) can help. Never use force when opening or closing the hinge; this can damage the mechanism permanently. If the hinge remains stiff despite cleaning and light lubrication, professional jeweller servicing may be necessary.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Will this 9K gold ring tarnish?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>9K gold naturally resists tarnishing due to its high gold content (37.5% pure gold). However, environmental factors—chlorine from swimming, harsh chemicals, prolonged moisture exposure, and extreme temperatures—can cause oxidation and dull the finish over time. This is not true tarnishing but rather a natural patina or dulling. Proper storage (dry, separate from other jewellery) and simple maintenance (soap and water, thorough drying) prevent significant dulling. If dulling occurs, a soft microfibre cloth restores shine. Professional polishing by a jeweller addresses more significant finish changes.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Is this ring waterproof?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>9K gold is water-resistant but not fully waterproof. You can wear this ring while washing hands, showering, or swimming in freshwater. However, avoid chlorinated pools, salt water (which accelerates oxidation), and prolonged water exposure. Chlorine and saltwater are particularly harsh on gold finishes and can affect the hinge mechanism's smoothness. After water exposure, rinse with fresh water, dry thoroughly, and ensure the hinge moves freely. For extended water activities, remove the ring and store it safely.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            How long does a 9K gold clicker ring last?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>With proper care, a 9K gold hinged clicker ring lasts decades. The durability of 9K gold actually exceeds higher-purity golds (14K, 18K) because the alloy metals strengthen the structure and the hinge mechanism remains responsive for 5–10+ years with regular use. Occasional professional maintenance (cleaning and hinge inspection by a jeweller) extends lifespan further. As a precious metal piece, this ring becomes part of your permanent jewellery collection. Many people pass heirloom gold pieces through generations.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Can I resize or modify this ring?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>9K gold is technically resizable, but modification is generally not recommended for hinged clicker rings. Resizing involves cutting and adding metal, which disrupts the hinge mechanism and can affect structural integrity. If you discover your gauge or diameter isn't quite right, contacting Monster Piercing to exchange for a different size is simpler and safer than attempting modification. For unique customization or bespoke modifications, contact us to discuss professional jeweller options. A qualified jeweller experienced with hinged mechanisms can assess whether specific modifications are feasible.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What about returns and exchanges?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Not specified in provided data. Please visit our returns policy page or contact Monster Piercing customer service for complete details on product returns, exchanges, and satisfaction guarantees. We want you to feel confident in your purchase.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Which gold finish is best for my skin tone?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>All three finishes—yellow gold, white gold, and rose gold—work beautifully across different skin undertones. Yellow gold creates warmth on warm, olive, or golden skin and pairs beautifully with earth-tone clothing. White gold appears contemporary and refined on fair or cool-toned skin and complements neutral, cool-toned outfits. Rose gold is universally flattering across all skin undertones and adds romantic warmth to any aesthetic. Consider which colour you wear most often in other jewellery to ensure coordination. Personal preference ultimately matters most—all three are equally durable and hypoallergenic.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Can I wear this if I have a nickel allergy?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>This 9K gold hinged clicker ring is designed to be nickel-free or nickel-minimal (trace amounts below allergenic thresholds). However, if you have a confirmed nickel allergy or extreme metal sensitivity, contact Monster Piercing before purchasing to verify exact alloy composition. Some individuals with severe nickel allergies react even to trace amounts. In those cases, implant-grade titanium or solid platinum may be safer alternatives. Never assume nickel absence without confirmation—your health and comfort depend on accurate material information.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            How do I know if my piercing is fully healed?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Healing duration varies by location: nostril piercings typically heal in 4–6 weeks, septum piercings in 6–8 weeks, and cartilage piercings in 8–12 weeks or longer. Signs of full healing include: the piercing channel feels stable with no movement or tenderness, minimal or no discharge, no active redness or swelling, and the jewellery sits securely without rotating. Your original piercer is the best source for confirming full healing—they understand your piercing's specific timeline. Do not assume healing based on appearance alone; internal healing can lag behind external appearance. Inserting new jewellery too early risks infection and complications.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What if I experience irritation after inserting this ring?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>If you experience redness, swelling, discharge, itching, or pain after insertion, remove the ring immediately. Irritation can indicate: incorrect gauge or diameter for your piercing, incomplete healing, sensitivity to alloy metals, or early infection. Rinse with warm saline water and allow the piercing to rest without jewellery for 24–48 hours. If irritation persists, consult a healthcare provider or your original piercer. Do not reinsert the ring until irritation completely resolves. Persistent or worsening symptoms require medical attention—piercing infections can become serious if ignored.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Is this ring suitable for everyday active wear?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Yes. The 9K gold hinged clicker ring is designed for all-day, active lifestyle wear. The smooth hinged mechanism doesn't snag on clothing or hair, and the lightweight gold doesn't create pressure points or discomfort during exercise, work, or outdoor activities. The implant-grade material resists skin reactions even with sweat exposure. Simply rinse after workouts and dry thoroughly to maintain finish quality. This ring is built to adapt to your lifestyle, not demand special handling.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Can I layer multiple clicker rings in one ear?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Absolutely. The classic segment design and consistent 9K gold finish make this ring ideal for layering. Position multiple rings across helix, daith, and conch placements for a curated aesthetic. Space them evenly for sophisticated balance or cluster in the upper cartilage for bolder visual impact. The versatile sizing options (three gauges, seven diameters) ensure you can find the right fit for each piercing. Mix and match finishes—yellow, white, and rose gold all coordinate beautifully together.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n  </ul>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>"
      }
    },
